## 5. Tactical Deception & The Long Game
 * **The Hidden Profile:** Kaelen strictly masks his true progression. He deliberately configures his outward appearance, gear, and combat habits to mimic a standard, low-performing Tier-E *Salvager*.
 * **Controlled Output:** Even when his internal stats reach Tier-C or Tier-B levels, he will only display a fraction of his capabilities in public—using just enough strength to complete a job or survive, passing it off as "lucky timing," "using cheap environmental traps," or "fluking a critical hit."
 * **The Absolute Threshold:** Kaelen establishes a hard rule for himself: **Total secrecy until he achieves Tier-S or Tier-SS equivalence.** Until he possesses the raw, unclassified destructive capacity to completely obliterate anyone who tries to capture him, he remains a ghost in the system. If an academy instructor or a guild scout looks his way, all they will ever see is a broke student scraping by on odd jobs.
The pieces are perfectly aligned now. The tension isn't just about him surviving the monsters anymore—it's about him hiding his explosive growth from the very society he lives in.